Final keyword:
final keyword in java is used to show that something is completed and don't need any modification
-with variables to indicate that the value of this variable is final
-we can use it with methods to show that method implementation is final and it cannot be overriden
by child classes
-with classes so that no class can inherit from that class

Final with variables:
-always try to make your variables as final if possible (helps reduce bugs)
-widely used with static keyword

A<-B<-C<-D<-


Final keyword can be used with a class, variable and a method. it restricts any further modification

